The paper deals with anomaly detection in Process Control Systems (PCSs), which is a critical infrastructure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes an approach based on Multivariate Statistical Process Control (MSPC), which is a technique used in control systems engineering. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for monitoring process level and controller level data, which suggests that it may belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the use of network level data for anomaly detection, which suggests that it may also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
